            <title>[SPARK-2435] Add shutdown hook to bin/pyspark</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2435</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We currently never stop the SparkContext cleanly in bin/pyspark unless the user explicitly runs sc.stop(). This behavior is not consistent with bin/spark-shell, in which case Ctrl+D stops the SparkContext before quitting the shell.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
